songs.title: Calling Me Out
songs.lyrics:
[Chorus]
I swear, I swear
We all need a little love sometimes
I swear, you're calling me, calling me out
I swear, we all need a little love sometimes
I swear, you're calling me, calling me out

[Verse 1]
Lightey, looking like a wifey
I press the blue button and I follow that
I ain't gonna lie she a 10 10 but she ain't too peng for a follow back
And she living life like she single
But if anybody ask her she got a man
A chick saw me whippin excursion and
Now the same girl wanna holla man

[Pre-Chorus]
But please don't draw me out, I ask nicely
None of them girls they ain't wifey
And they wanna talk and talk about ex's
None of them man they ain't like me, nah
You can't draw me out, I'm too cautious
None of them girls are flawless
And they wanna talk and talk about ex's
None of them man they ain't

[Chorus]
I swear, I swear
We all need a little love sometimes
I swear, you're calling me, calling me out
I swear, we all need a little love sometimes
I swear, you're calling me, calling me out

[Verse 2]
Telling me you gotta be working
But also you gotta make time for me
If we never go where I want
Then why do girls ask what I'd like to eat
And she wanna pay when I turn around
I can't let her stand in the line for me
I smiled when she pulled out her Barclays
Sorry, it's the 419 in me

[Pre-Chorus]
But please don't draw me out, I ask nicely
None of them girls they ain't wifey
And they wanna talk and talk about ex's
None of them man they ain't like me, nah
You can't draw me out, I'm too cautious
None of them girls are flawless
And they wanna talk and talk about ex's
None of them man they ain't

[Chorus]
I swear, I swear
We all need a little love sometimes
I swear, you're calling me, calling me out
I swear, we all need a little love sometimes
I swear, you're calling me, calling me out
You're calling me, calling me out
You're calling me, calling me out
You're calling me, calling me out
You're calling me, calling me out
